cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CC 

This paper discusses the design and optimization of recurrent neural networks for sequence indexing and working memory, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of reservoir computing and vector symbolic architectures, which are related to topics in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses memory buffers and forgetting mechanisms, which are related to topics in cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
